# 1.3 Command Creating

Creating a command is quite simple using 2 packages
- fs.js
- SlashCommandBuilder (Discord.js)

```
const { SlashCommandBuilder } = require('discord.js');
const { fs } = require("node:fs")
if(!fs.existsSync('./logs/commands/'){
fs.mkdirSync('./logs/commands/')
}
module.exports = {
	data: new SlashCommandBuilder()
		.setName('ping')
		.setDescription('Replies with Pong! '),
	async execute(interaction) {
          interaction.reply("Pong");
        fs.writeFileSync('./logs/commands/discord.ping.json',`{\n"Name": "Ping", \n "Output": "Pong"}
        })	
	},
};
```
